<HEADLINE>
NEW CHIEF FOR NEW YORK TIMES MAGAZINE GROUP
</HEADLINE>
&LR; (ll) &QL;
&UR; c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service &QC; &LR; &QL;

<TEXT>
Leonard Forman has been named president and chief executive of
The New York Times Co.'s magazine group, the company announced on
Monday.
Formerly senior vice president for corporate development,
Forman, 53, succeeds James Fitzgerald, 59, who will serve in an
advisory role as chairman of the magazine group for one year.
Forman will be responsible for the magazine group's publications:
Golf Digest, Golf World and Golf Shop Operations. He will report to
Russell Lewis, president and chief executive of the Times Co.
The Times Co. publishes The New York Times, The Boston Globe, 21
regional newspapers and three magazines. It also operates
television and radio stations as well as news, photo, graphic and
electronic publishing services.
